{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "Addresses [this](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gui/issues/35/scene3d-memory-leak-on-resize) Ignition GUI issue when resizing the window.\r\n\r\nThis PR improves the situation, but I can still see some leak.\r\n\r\nCommenting out the call to `this->RebuildViewport` fixes the leak, so I think it's something there. It seems that we're creating a new `ogreViewport` every time, but I'd expect that removing the previous target and removing all viewports of the new target should take care of this?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Addresses <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gui/issues/35/scene3d-memory-leak-on-resize\" rel=\"nofollow\">this</a> Ignition GUI issue when resizing the window.</p>\n<p>This PR improves the situation, but I can still see some leak.</p>\n<p>Commenting out the call to <code>this-&gt;RebuildViewport</code> fixes the leak, so I think it's something there. It seems that we're creating a new <code>ogreViewport</code> every time, but I'd expect that removing the previous target and removing all viewports of the new target should take care of this?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Improve target rebuilding", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Improve target rebuilding</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "Addresses [this](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gui/issues/35/scene3d-memory-leak-on-resize) Ignition GUI issue when resizing the window.\r\n\r\nThis PR improves the situation, but I can still see some leak.\r\n\r\nCommenting out the call to `this->RebuildViewport` fixes the leak, so I think it's something there. It seems that we're creating a new `ogreViewport` every time, but I'd expect that removing the previous target and removing all viewports of the new target should take care of this?", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pullrequests/108/decline"}, "diffstat": {"href": "https://api